advisory: The tqdm._version module in tqdm versions before 4.11.2 allows local users to execute arbitrary code via a crafted repo with a malicious git log in the current working directory.

Imageio 2.6.0 fixes a code injection vulnerability for Windows users that have dcmtk installed, and where an attacker can set the filename.
https://github.com/imageio/imageio/commit/5b398716d518cd14e8b978ea3cd8ec6c0236c1d8
The scipy.weave component in SciPy before 0.12.1 creates insecure temporary directories.

Torch 1.13.1 includes a fix for CVE-2022-45907: In PyTorch before trunk/89695, torch.jit.annotations.parse_type_line can cause arbitrary code execution because eval is used unsafely.
https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/88868
